<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,295,754]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
The genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Weksler, Percequillo &amp; Voss" authorityYear="2006" box="[276,407,295,321]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Aegialomys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[276,407,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Aegialomys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
comprises four species, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Allen 1897)" baseAuthorityName="Allen" baseAuthorityYear="1897" box="[687,948,295,321]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Aegialomys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="baroni">
<emphasis box="[687,793,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">A. baroni</emphasis>
(Allen 1897)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Waterhouse 1839)" baseAuthorityName="Waterhouse" baseAuthorityYear="1839" box="[961,1377,295,321]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Aegialomys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="galapagoensis">
<emphasis box="[961,1155,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">A. galapagoensis</emphasis>
(Waterhouse 1839)
</taxonomicName>
(that includes 
<taxonomicName authority="(Allen 1892))" authorityName="" baseAuthorityName="Allen" baseAuthorityYear="1892" box="[251,503,331,357]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Aegialomys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bauri">
<emphasis box="[251,342,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">A. bauri</emphasis>
(Allen 1892))
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Osgood 1944)" baseAuthorityName="Osgood" baseAuthorityYear="1944" box="[514,755,331,357]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Aegialomys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ica">
<emphasis box="[514,578,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">A. ica</emphasis>
(Osgood 1944)
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Thomas 1894)" baseAuthorityName="Thomas" baseAuthorityYear="1894" box="[812,1158,331,357]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Aegialomys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="xanthaeolus">
<emphasis box="[812,978,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">A. xanthaeolus</emphasis>
(Thomas 1894)
</taxonomicName>
, that inhabit the northern Trans-Andean South America, in a region that extends from centralâ€“southern 
<collectingCountry box="[1026,1119,367,393]" name="Ecuador" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
to Southern 
<collectingCountry box="[1265,1319,368,394]" name="Peru" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Peru</collectingCountry>
, including in its range the Galapagos Archipelago (
<bibRefCitation author="Weksler, M. &amp; Percequillo, A. R. &amp; Voss, R. S." box="[605,830,403,430]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" pagination="1 - 29" refId="ref76039" refString="Weksler, M., Percequillo, A. R. &amp; Voss, R. S. (2006) Ten new genera of oryzomyine rodents (Cricetidae: Sigmodontinae). Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History, 3537, 1 - 29." type="journal article" year="2006">
Weksler 
<emphasis box="[706,756,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">et al</emphasis>
. 2006
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Prado, J. R. &amp; Percequillo, A. R." box="[842,1139,403,429]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" pagination="1 - 120" refId="ref72147" refString="Prado, J. R. &amp; Percequillo, A. R. (2013) Geographic distribution of the genera of the tribe Oryzomyini (Rodentia: Cricetidae: Sigmodontinae) in South America: patterns of distribution and diversity. Archivos de Zoologia, 44 (1), 1 - 120. https: // doi. org / 10.11606 / issn. 2176 - 7793. v 44 i 1 p 1 - 120" type="journal article" year="2013">Prado &amp; Percequillo 2013</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Percequillo, A. R." box="[1152,1359,403,430]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" pagination="293 - 298" refId="ref71159" refString="Percequillo, A. R. (2015 a) Genus Aegialomys Weksler, Percequillo &amp; Voss, 2006. In: Patton, J., Pardinas, U. F. J. &amp; D'Elia, G. (Eds.), Mammals of South America. 2. Rodents. University of Chicago Press, Chicago, Illinois, pp. 293 - 298." type="book chapter" year="2015">Percequillo 2015a</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Prado, J. R. &amp; Percequillo, A. R." pageId="6" pageNumber="7" pagination="477 - 498" refId="ref72225" refString="Prado, J. R. &amp; Percequillo, A. R. (2016) Systematic studies of the genus Aegialomys Weksler, Percequillo and Voss, 2006 (Rodentia: Cricetidae: Sigmodontinae): Annotated catalogue of the types of the species-group taxa. Zootaxa, 4144 (4), 477 - 498. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4144.4.2" type="journal article" year="2016">Prado &amp; Percequillo 2016</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Prado, J. R. &amp; Percequillo, A. R." box="[384,680,439,465]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" pagination="71 - 118" refId="ref72295" refString="Prado, J. R. &amp; Percequillo, A. R. (2018) Systematic studies of the genus Aegialomys Weksler et al., 2006 (Rodentia: Cricetidae: Sigmodontinae): geographic variation, species delimitation, and biogeography. Journal of Mammalian Evolution, 25 (1), 71 - 118. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / s 10914 - 016 - 9360 - y" type="journal article" year="2018">Prado &amp; Percequillo 2018</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Gardner, A. L. &amp; Patton, J. L." box="[697,977,439,466]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" pagination="1 - 48" refId="ref67114" refString="Gardner, A. L. &amp; Patton, J. L. (1976) Karyotypic variation in Oryzomyine rodents (Cricetinae) with comments on chromosomal evolution in the Neotropical Cricetine complex. Occasional papers of the Museum of Zoology, 49, 1 - 48." type="journal article" year="1976">Gardner &amp; Patton (1976)</bibRefCitation>
described the karyotypes of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="" baseAuthorityName="Allen" baseAuthorityYear="1892" box="[1298,1390,439,465]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Aegialomys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bauri">
<emphasis box="[1298,1390,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">A. bauri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Thomas" baseAuthorityYear="1894" box="[151,318,475,501]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Aegialomys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="xanthaeolus">
<emphasis box="[151,318,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">A. xanthaeolus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as essentially identical in all aspects (2n = 56, FN = 58). However, the same specimens karyotyped and identified as 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Thomas" baseAuthorityYear="1894" box="[339,504,511,537]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Aegialomys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="xanthaeolus">
<emphasis box="[339,504,511,537]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">A. xanthaeolus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Gardner, A. L. &amp; Patton, J. L." box="[543,820,511,538]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" pagination="1 - 48" refId="ref67114" refString="Gardner, A. L. &amp; Patton, J. L. (1976) Karyotypic variation in Oryzomyine rodents (Cricetinae) with comments on chromosomal evolution in the Neotropical Cricetine complex. Occasional papers of the Museum of Zoology, 49, 1 - 48." type="journal article" year="1976">Gardner &amp; Patton (1976)</bibRefCitation>
were recently reviewed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Prado, J. R. &amp; Percequillo, A. R." box="[1123,1432,511,538]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" pagination="477 - 498" refId="ref72225" refString="Prado, J. R. &amp; Percequillo, A. R. (2016) Systematic studies of the genus Aegialomys Weksler, Percequillo and Voss, 2006 (Rodentia: Cricetidae: Sigmodontinae): Annotated catalogue of the types of the species-group taxa. Zootaxa, 4144 (4), 477 - 498. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4144.4.2" type="journal article" year="2016">Prado &amp; Percequillo (2016)</bibRefCitation>
, highlighting that these specimens belong to 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Allen" baseAuthorityYear="1897" box="[642,746,547,573]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Aegialomys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="baroni">
<emphasis box="[642,746,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">A. baroni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Osgood" baseAuthorityYear="1944" box="[799,864,547,573]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Aegialomys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ica">
<emphasis box="[799,864,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">A. ica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Moreover, as 
<bibRefCitation author="Prado, J. R. &amp; Percequillo, A. R." box="[1031,1340,547,573]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" pagination="71 - 118" refId="ref72295" refString="Prado, J. R. &amp; Percequillo, A. R. (2018) Systematic studies of the genus Aegialomys Weksler et al., 2006 (Rodentia: Cricetidae: Sigmodontinae): geographic variation, species delimitation, and biogeography. Journal of Mammalian Evolution, 25 (1), 71 - 118. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / s 10914 - 016 - 9360 - y" type="journal article" year="2018">Prado &amp; Percequillo (2018)</bibRefCitation>
synonymized 
<taxonomicName authorityName="" baseAuthorityName="Allen" baseAuthorityYear="1892" box="[227,319,583,609]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Aegialomys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bauri">
<emphasis box="[227,319,583,609]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">A. bauri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
under 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Waterhouse" baseAuthorityYear="1839" box="[396,589,583,609]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Aegialomys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="galapagoensis">
<emphasis box="[396,589,583,609]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">A. galapagoensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the karyotype of the former was attributed tentatively to the latter.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,295,754]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
Karyotype: 2n = 56 and FN = 58. Autosomal complement: two small metacentric and submetacentric pairs, and 25 acrocentric pairs (one distinctly large and the remaining large to small decreasing in size). Sex chromosomes: X, a large acrocentric; Y, a small acrocentric (
<bibRefCitation author="Gardner, A. L. &amp; Patton, J. L." box="[618,881,691,718]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" pagination="1 - 48" refId="ref67114" refString="Gardner, A. L. &amp; Patton, J. L. (1976) Karyotypic variation in Oryzomyine rodents (Cricetinae) with comments on chromosomal evolution in the Neotropical Cricetine complex. Occasional papers of the Museum of Zoology, 49, 1 - 48." type="journal article" year="1976">Gardner &amp; Patton 1976</bibRefCitation>
, pp. 6, 
<figureCitation box="[959,1047,691,717]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1191,1215]" captionTargetBox="[159,1426,281,1162]" captionTargetId="figure-69@7.[151,1436,273,1168]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 2. Distribution of diploid and fundamental number of karyotyped specimens of genus Cerradomys. (â–¡) C. akroai; (â– ) C. goytaca; (Ãª) C. langguthi; (r) C. maracajuensis; (â–²) C. marinhus; (â—‹) C. scotti; (â˜†) C. subflavus; (l) C. vivoi." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4423619" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4423619/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Fig. 2D</figureCitation>
). The karyotypes of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Thomas" baseAuthorityYear="1894" box="[1271,1436,691,717]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Aegialomys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="xanthaeolus">
<emphasis box="[1271,1436,691,717]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">A. xanthaeolus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was currently unknown.
</paragraph>
